rComments: Ok saying you're going to help us with what material to focus on for exams & then bombarding us by saying  everything will be tested is NOT helpful! It's stressful & a waste of time. Don't need to go to class, everything's read word-for-word off slides/ need to study though. Guests are decent. Disappointed, used to be so excited for this class...
Very disorganized. Makes many mistakes on exam questions, not very clear during the lecture. At least she grades easily.

Very kind lady... Get's a hard time from students for grammar mistakes but it was her first time teaching the course so she will most likely fix things up for future years... Exams, quizzes and assignments were always easy/fair and the average for all of them were around 80%. Also, what's great is you get the grade you deserve!

Might be a decent teacher in an english class, but makes numerous translating  mistakes that leaves the students wondering what she actually means. Teachers should show an example by NOT using wikipedia as a source, since our papers would most likely get thrown out for it. Teacher never had time to finish half her slides in a single class.

Great teacher, first time teaching the class. Made herself available for questions. Exams were either easy or fair, never too hard. Her exams were based entirely on her notes and classes so the book was a waste of money for me.
